                   <h3>Delete cookies</h3>
                   <p>Do you want to delete all cookies on your computer? No problem. But keep in mind that by removing cookies you will experience less user convenience when you visit websites. Certain settings will no longer be saved and you may miss out on relevant offers. Incidentally, cookies will be stored on your computer, tablet or mobile after every internet visit, unless you have blocked the placement of new cookies.</p>
                       <p>The settings for removing cookies can be found in the toolbar of your browser. You can read more about this on the websites of the browsers <a href="http://windows.microsoft.com/nl-be/windows-vista/Delete-your-Internet-cookies">Internet Explorer</a>, <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/delete-cookies-remove-info-websites-stored">Mozilla Firefox</a> or <a href="http://support.google.com/chrome/bin/answer.py?hl=nl&answer=95647">Google Chrome</a>. Do you use Safari? Safari blocks advertiser cookies by default. You can change this setting by clicking on the symbol for settings at the top right. Then go to 'Preferences', tab 'Privacy'. You can then choose from 3 settings.</p>
